#instruction for the nasa project 
1.0 create a fork of the repository in your github 

2.0 create an instance using amazon cloud services

3.0 get inside your instance by ssh -i .ssh/(the key) ubuntu@(IP Address).

4.0 update the system by
sudo apt update -y
sudo apt upgrade -y

5.0 install python and required tools:
sudo apt install python3 python3-pip python3-venv git nginx -y

6.0 to check the verions you must type: 
python3 --version
pip3 --version
git --version

7.0 your VM has all the dependancies and now you can clone it to the github you have created
git clone https://github.com/raminafsari/nasa-flask-app.git
 8.0 create a python virtual environment by
sudo python3 -m venv venv

9.0 to activate it 
source venv/bin/activate
the shell must now show (venv)

10.0 install pythn dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

11.0 download gunicorn seperately as it is not in the requirements.txt but it is still needed
pip install gunicorn

12.0 now you must go to the provided link in nasas website and register a free api key
13.0 then you se the api key environment variable

export NASA_API_KEY=abc123xyz
14.0 to verify
echo $NASA_API_KEY

15.0 run the flask app
python app.py 
16.0 the app was not working with Ip address:5000 due to the fact that the security froup in the instance did not have this port ready/
make sure the security group is updated/

17.0 now the app should work but when you control c it stope as you need gunicorn to run on the page.
pip install gunicorn

18.0to run the gunicorn on the background you need to 
gunicorn --bind 0.0.0.0:5000 app:app

19.0 configuring nginx reverse proxy
sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/nasa-app
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name _;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:5000;

        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
    }
}
save it and exit

20.0 enable site 
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/nasa-app /etc/nginx/sites-enabled

21.0 test confiq
sudo nginx -t

22.0 restart nginx
sudo systemctl restart nginx

23.0Run Gunicorn in Background Using systemd (Recommended)
Create a systemd Service
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/nasa-app.service
inside write :
[Unit]
Description=NASA Flask App Gunicorn Service
After=network.target

[Service]
User=ubuntu
WorkingDirectory=/home/ubuntu/nasa-flask-app
Environment="NASA_API_KEY=5VxO96gpXO8X6p9LdheqLjFt9dmVdLGJa6YbS7Y3"
ExecStart=/home/ubuntu/nasa-flask-app/venv/bin/gunicorn --workers 3 --bind 127.0.0.1:5000 app:app
Restart=always

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

save and exit


24.0 reload systemd
sudo systemctl daemon-reload

25.0enable systemt1 enable nasa-app
sudo systemctl enable nasa-app
 
26.0start the service
sudo systemctl start nasa-app

27.0 check the status of nasa-app
sudo systemctl status nasa-app
